# ===========================================================================
# Waruka .gitignore
#
# The committed repo is the SOURCE tree: the waruka/ package, vendored
# third-party model *code*, build scripts, docs, icons, and the legal files.
# Everything excluded below is one of:
#   - large binary model weights  -> delivered via GitHub Releases / upstream
#                                    (see BUILDING.md); GitHub rejects any
#                                    single file > 100 MB without Git LFS.
#   - build / packaging output    -> dist/, build/, *.spec, __pycache__
#   - local development scratch   -> dev/, runtime JSON/MP4 artefacts
#   - editor / agent metadata     -> .claude/
#   - per-user data               -> project.json calibration tied to private
#                                    footage the public repo doesn't ship.
#
# NOTE: keep every comment on its OWN line. A '#' after a pattern is NOT a
# comment in .gitignore -- it becomes part of the pattern and silently
# breaks the rule.
# ===========================================================================

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.venv/
venv/

# --- Build / packaging output ---
/build/
/dist/

# waruka.spec / waruka-cli.spec are regenerated by build_exe.py
*.spec

# --- Development scratch (clips, runs, handovers, diagnostics, ~11 GB) ---
/dev/

# --- Editor / agent metadata ---
.claude/

# --- Logs & progress sidecars ---
*.log
/logs/
.waruka_progress_*
_progress.json

# --- Runtime pipeline artefacts (regenerated per run) ---
/project.json
/project_*.json
tracks_*.json
players_*.json
campath_*.json
*.mp4
_viz_*.png

# pipeline artefact output, created next to source videos when a job runs
waruka_tracking/

# scratch diagnostic images at repo root
/_*.png

# --- Model weights (delivered via GitHub Releases / upstream; see BUILDING.md) ---
# GitHub hard-rejects files > 100 MB without Git LFS; these are large and
# only needed for the optional interpolate / upscale / --sr stages.
*.pt
*.pth
*.pkl
*.onnx

# except the small core YOLO detector (5.6 MB) which the base pipeline needs
!/yolo11n.pt

# 135 MB TensorFlow SavedModel (alternate FILM format, unused by the bundle)
/third_party/film_l1_saved_model/

# rife_4_25.zip weights archive
/third_party/rife/*.zip

# --- Vendored upstream demo / test media (not needed to run Waruka) ---
/third_party/film/photos/
/third_party/rife/demo/
/third_party/realesrgan/inputs/
/third_party/realesrgan/assets/
/third_party/realesrgan/tests/
/third_party/realesrgan/experiments/
